cs.LG, cs.IOT, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.DB 

The paper focuses on the application of deep learning techniques for IoT data analytics, which falls under the intersection of several CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper discusses various deep learning architectures and algorithms. The second likely category is cs.IOT (Internet of Things), as the paper specifically focuses on IoT data analytics. The third likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as deep learning is a subset of AI. The fourth likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper discusses the characteristics of IoT data and the challenges of processing big data and streaming data. The fifth likely category is cs.DB (Databases), as the paper discusses the implementation of DL on fog and cloud centers to support IoT applications.
